Benchmarking Your Security Program
Objectives
By the end of this lab, students will be able to:

Understand security program maturity assessment frameworks and methodologies
Install and configure a benchmarking environment on Linux
Analyze security program maturity using standardized metrics
Develop Python scripts to automate security benchmarking processes
Generate maturity reports and identify improvement opportunities
Prerequisites
Basic understanding of cybersecurity frameworks (NIST, ISO 27001)
Fundamental Linux command-line skills
Python programming basics (functions, loops, file I/O)
Understanding of security governance concepts
Lab Environment
Al Nafi provides pre-configured Ubuntu 22.04 LTS cloud machines. Click Start Lab to access your environment with:

Python 3.10 and pip pre-installed
Network connectivity for package downloads
Text editors (nano, vim) available
